opean Union and its externalization to Sub-Saharan Africa, she provides insight in the still understudied issue of people's everyday life after forced returns, exemplifying the effects of intra-African and European deportation regimes and the reactions to them. In doing so, this ethnographic study creates empirical knowledge on key issues in migration research, policy, and practice in a charged debate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aAfrica. 4aCultural Anthropology. 4aDeportation. 4aEthnology. 4aFleeing. 4aImmobility. 4aMali. 4aMobility. 4aPost-Deportation. 4aRefugee Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAfrica.  aCultural Anthropology.  aDeportation.  aEthnology.  aFleeing.  aImmobility.  aMali.  aMobility.  aPost-Deportation.  aRefugee Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z978311076731508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022z978311076851040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839460092zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839460092/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076731-5 transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-076851-0 transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA